title: The World of Babies
description: Focuses on how infants learn about intuitive physics, naive psychology, and shared culture. Also discusses how cultural communities shape infants' learning. Satisfies the seminar requirement. Satisfies the senior comprehensive requirement.

conditions.restricted_to_majors: senior psychology and cognitive science majors.

pre_req_data.text: Prerequisite(s): satisfaction of Entry Level Writing and Composition requirements and PSYC 100.  Enrollment is restricted to senior psychology and cognitive science majors.
